---

Bring a #pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{}. Halve, peel, and
thinly slice the @Yellow Onion{1}. Remove ribs and stems from the @Swiss Chard{1%bunch}
and thinly slice. Slice the chard leaves into ribbons. Mince or grate the @Garlic{2%cloves}.

Add the swiss chard stems to the boiling water. Cook for ~{2%minutes}, then add the
leaves to the pot. Cook for about ~{1%minute} until wilted. Remove with a #slotted spoon{}
and set aside. Keep the pot on the stove, we'll be using it for the pasta.

Heat @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #non-stick pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion
and season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook for about ~{5%minutes}, until slightly softened.

While the onions cook, add the @Penne Pasta{6%ounce} to the boiling water and cook
for ~{9-10%minutes}, until al dente.

Meanwhile, add the @Mixed Wild Mushrooms{4%ounce} to the pan with the onions and season
with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, tossing, for about ~{5%minutes}, until slightly golden
brown. Add the garlic, @Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon}, and as many @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon}
as you dare. Cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Add the @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon} and 1/4 cup of pasta water to the pan. Stir to combine.
Cook until slightly thickened, about ~{2%minutes}.

Drain the pasta and add it to the pan with the sauce. Add the chard stems and leaves
and toss to combine.

Serve the pasta with a sprinkle of @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup} on top!

> Garlicky wild mushrooms and swiss chard are front and center in this creamy pasta. We've
> spiced it up with a sprinkle of paprika and a dash of chili flakes. Parmesan cheese does
> the trick to make this penne a real winner.